rComments: He's extremely liberal and makes no attempt to hide it in class.  If your're conservative (or even moderate) or pro-chief, you'll probably want to kick this guy in the nuts by the end of the semester.  Hates white people.

Sexy man. VERY laid back and finds deep meaning in everything you say. Lots of papers but he makes them easy to write. Gives extensions on papers a lot/post pones reading assignments. I'd definitely take another one of his classes if I could

Roediger was my first professor at U of I, and the best.  He taught history through a different perspective.  Reading not necessary, but interesting.  Very interesting lectures. You will NOT fall asleep.  He is a great, caring and sweet guy.  Very intelligent and great to learn from. I wish I could go back and take another class from him.

I thought I was taking a history class, but instead I got a class that should be called Conspiracy Theories and Revisionist History. He proposed wacked-out theories and doesn't bother to back them up other than we are supposed to know his intellectual superiority over us. I am a history buff and have never heard any of his theories before.
Roedgier is a "the chillest guy I know" as my TA used to say. This class is easy as long as you get the arguments from lectures. Lectures get really boring, but the tests are easy.
An award winning professor, Roediger really knows History. Lectures are important, and writing papers in highlighted.

roedy knows his stuff, almost to well. it seems like he wants to teach so much, yet doesnt have the time. lectures are necessary. everything works towards two papers & an inclass midterm essay. overhead notes could be more organized, but he's not hard to follow.

The notes are not posted online and he usually deviates from the outline anyway, so you sort of have to go to class.  However, to be honest, i really don't mind.  He has a nice voice and he tells history in a such a comical and interesting way. The class views history from unique angles.
this man is brillant and an awesome professor even if his class is hard i would still recomend taking it

His course is the very best I've ever taken.  He has a humility and kindness that is rare in professors, and a brilliance that truly shines.  His courses will challenge you to think in more creative and complex ways.
